> PS. If you&#x27;re coming from a Unix background and interested in learning posh: <a href="https://certsimple.com/rosetta-stone" rel="nofollow">https://certsimple.com/rosetta-stone</a><p>I stopped reading this when I got to this part:<p><pre><code>    whois &#x27;domain [domain name]&#x27;
</code></pre>
--><p><pre><code>    $web = New-WebServiceProxy &#x27;http://www.webservicex.net/whois.asmx?WSDL&#x27;
    $web.GetWhoIs(&#x27;[domain name]&#x27;)
</code></pre>
It&#x27;s cute that there is some kind of VBScript for calling web services, but this line tells me that this document must have been authored by some kind of PowerShell apologist.<p>Just put <i>none</i> in the `whois` box and move on.
